      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI MARK (9) made a nice return at his latest appearance last week when he raced parked but stuck on and finished 2.7 metres away in third at Bendigo. That continued his good form from last campaign and he should be better for it. Winning chance if things go his way from the back row. TOPHUT JOHNY (2) was out of the placings but only beaten 7 metres at Bendigo last start. Has placed in four of eight tries at this circuit and distance and draws for a good showing. PRECIOUS BELLE NZ (7) draws wide but with even luck she is a player following a 1.2m second from the back row at her most recent appearance at Charlton. RINGER RUSS (5) will be rock-hard fit after four starts back from a spell and has claims off a Shepparton placing three back.",
